erit','closed','closed','','49-revision-v1','','','2018-01-06 06:51:29','2018-01-06 11:51:29','',49,'http://derulski.local/blog/uncategorized/49-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(180,1,'2018-01-09 13:34:56','2018-01-09 18:34:56','<header class=\"entry-header\">\n<h1 class=\"entry-title\"><strong style=\"font-size: 16px;\">PRIVACY STATEMENT</strong></h1>\n</header>\n<div class=\"entry-content\">\n\nLast Revised: December 16, 2017\n\nSaxophone Technique (âWeâ) is committed to protecting the privacy of your personal information and complies with theÂ <em>Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act</em>Â (PIPEDA.)\n\nWe also comply with theÂ <em>Canadian Anti-Spam LegislationÂ </em>and will not solicit you by email without your express consent.\n\nWe seek to be open and transparent about the information our website may collect about your activity on this site, the technology you use, and how we may use this information.\n\n<strong>WHAT DO WE DO WITH YOUR INFORMATION?</strong>\n\nWhen you browse our website, we automatically receive your computerâs Internet Protocol (IP) address in order to provide us with information that helps us learn about your browser and operating system. We use this information to ensure our website is compatible with, and optimized for â the technologies our users use.\n\nWe use 3rd party analytic services that help us learn how and when users use our website, and from which geographical regions they are from. We use this information to make design, content, and other decisions that improve our website in order to provide our users with more value and a better experience. We also use this information to monitor for any malicious, unlawful, or any activity that can be harmful to our users, the operation of our website, or the security, privacy, and integrity of any data under our control. We do not store or retain any data or information from site usage analytics that could be used to identify an individual without legal process.\n\nWith your permission, we may send you occasional emails about new content on our website, and other occasional marketing material. We will never send you emails without your express consent, and will always provide you with a simple one-step feature to unsubscribe from any of our mailing lists.\n\nWe only collect personal information that is voluntarily provided by you, and this information is only used for the purpose for which it was collected. Unless the purpose is self-evident due to the nature of the transaction in question, we will identify the purpose for which the personal information is collected at or before the time it is collected.\n\nWe retain any personal information you provide us only for the duration that is necessary to fulfill the purpose it was collected for.\n\n<strong>CONSENT</strong>\n\nHow do you get my consent?\n\nFor our subscription service, we use a double opt-in system to obtain your express consent. When you voluntarily subscribe to our website by providing us your email address into any form that is made evident and clear that the intent is to subscribe, you will receive a confirmation email that will require you to click a link contained in the message to confirm your subscription. Until you provide us with this confirmation, we assume that we do not have your consent, will not consider you as a subscriber, and will not send you any emails until such time in the future after you provide us with this confirmation.\n\nIf you decide to contact us using our contact form, we will reply to your inquiry to the email address you provided, and will only send you emails to fulfill and satisfy the context of your inquiry. Using our contact form does not imply any consent that you are subscribing to any of our mailing lists.\n\nHow do I withdraw my consent?\n\nIf after you opt-in you change your mind, you may withdraw your consent for us to contact you, for the continued collection, use, or disclosure of your information, at anytime, by contacting us at privacy@saxophonetechnique.ca or mailing us at: Saxophone Technique 308 Felan Ave, Oakville, ON, L6K 2X6, Canada\n\nYou may also use the unsubscribe link at the bottom of each email we send to our mailing lists, or use our contact form stating your intent to unsubscribe.\n\nWe will never pressure you for your reasons to unsubscribe, but we welcome your feedback so we may improve our service.\n\n<strong>DISCLOSURE</strong>\n\nWe never share or sell your personal information to any 3rd party unless we are required to do so by law.\n\n<strong>THIRD-PARTY SERVICES</strong>\n\nOccasionally, at our discretion, we may include or offer third-party products or services on our website. These third-party sites have separate and independent privacy policies. We therefore have no responsibility or liability for the content and activities of these linked sites. Nonetheless, we seek to protect the integrity of our site and welcome any feedback about the sites, services, or products we share.\n\n<strong>SECURITY</strong>\n\nTo protect your personal information, we take reasonable precautions and follow industry best practices to make sure it is not inappropriately lost, misused, accessed, disclosed, altered or destroyed.\n\nYour connection to our website is encrypted using secure socket layer technology (SSL). When you submit any data using a form on any of our webpages, it will be encrypted for and during its transit over the Internet to our database. We take the privacy and integrity of any data you submit to our website seriously and will always transmit and store it in a secure and responsible way. Although no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, we take all necessary steps to ensure the security of our website and the data it contains and collects meets or exceeds industry standards.\n\n<strong>COOKIES</strong>\n\nWe use cookies if you participate in a discussion by posting a comment, or have previously participated in a discussion on any of our webpages. The cookies are used to remember your name and email so you do not have to enter this information each time you choose to participate in a discussion.\n\nWe also use cookies on any webpage that contains a form so that when you submit data through it, we can verify the authenticity of the submission, i.e. it was submitted by you, from your computer, and not forged or spoofed by someone else, some automated bot, or other malicious intent.\n\nCookies provided by our website are stored in your browser on your computer, and our website requests the information it saved within them to make your experience more seamless. They are harmless, enhance your experience and security, and can only be accessed by our website. If you choose to disable cookies, any feature that requires authentication or user input will become unavailable to you, such as being able to login or submitting data using any input form. We are not forcing cookies on you, but certain features require them for security reasons. You will however be able to continue to browse and consume all content.\n\nWe also use cookies from our third party vendor Google Analytics which provides us with anonymous information about how you use our website. You can opt-out of Google Analytics for all sites by following theÂ <a href=\"https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/181881?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">instructions provided by Google</a>.\n\n<strong>CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY</strong>\n\nWe reserve the right to modify this privacy policy at any time, so please review it frequently. Changes and clarifications will take effect immediately upon their posting on the website. If we make material changes to this policy, we will notify you here that it has been updated, so that you are aware of what information we collect, how we use it, and under what circumstances, if any, we use and/or disclose it.\n\n<strong>QUESTIONS AND CONTACT INFORMATION</strong>\n\nIf you would like to access, correct, amend or delete any personal information we have about you, register a complaint, or simply want more information contact our Privacy Compliance Officer at privacy@saxophonetechnique.ca or by mail at Saxophone Technique\n\n[Re: Privacy Compliance Officer]\n\n[308 Felan Ave, Oakville, ON, L6K 2X6, Canada]\n\n</div>','Privacy Policy','','inherit','closed','closed','','49-autosave-v1','','','2018-01-09 13:34:56','2018-01-09 18:34:56','',49,'http://derulski.local/blog/uncategorized/49-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(181,1,'2018-01-09 13:36:22','2018-01-09 18:36:22','<header class=\"entry-header\">\r\n<h1 class=\"entry-title\"><strong style=\"font-size: 16px;\">PRIVACY STATEMENT</strong></h1>\r\n</header>\r\n<div class=\"entry-content\">\r\n\r\nLast Revised: January 9, 2017\r\n\r\n[company] (âWeâ) is committed to protecting the privacy of your personal information and complies with theÂ <em>Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act</em>Â (PIPEDA.)\r\n\r\nWe also comply with theÂ <em>Canadian Anti-Spam LegislationÂ </em>and will not solicit you by email without your express consent.\r\n\r\nWe seek to be open and transparent about the information our website may collect about your activity on this site, the technology you use, and how we may use this information.\r\n\r\n<strong>WHAT DO WE DO WITH YOUR INFORMATION?</strong>\r\n\r\nWhen you browse our website, we automatically receive your computerâs Internet Protocol (IP) address in order to provide us with information that helps us learn about your browser and operating system. We use this information to ensure our website is compatible with, and optimized for â the technologies our users use.\r\n\r\nWe use 3rd party analytic services that help us learn how and when users use our website, and from which geographical regions they are from. We use this information to make design, content, and other decisions that improve our website in order to provide our users with